    "body": "## Problem\n\nFrom the documentation (`:h vim.lsp.buf.code_action()`) `opts.context` has all its keys optional, but the source code expects [lsp.CodeActionContext.diagnostics to be an array](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/b351afb1b1c564c5a4e6856764d4db21a873242c/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_meta/protocol.lua#L3036).\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\nlua_ls gives a warning (\"Missing required fields in type `lsp.CodeActionContext`: `diagnostics`\") when doing\n```lua\n      vim.lsp.buf.code_action({\n        context = { only = source_actions },\n      })\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nThere shouldn't be a warning, as context.diagnostics is `Inferred from the current position if not provided.`\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.13.0-dev-237 g48d11681c2` neovim/neovim@48d11681c2\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.6.87.2-microsoft-standard-WSL2\n- Terminal name/version: WezTerm 20241007-103714-ed430415\n-  environment variable: `xterm-256color`\n- Installation: build from source\n\n",
